 BC-APTV Outlook,0872 

      APTV 1300 GMT OUTLOOK TUESDAY JUNE 2, 1998   For Planner / Newsdesk use - stories expected to move in the next 12 hours. All times are GMT.  ---- EXPECTED: ---- AFGHAN: QUAKE - APTV will have the latest pictures from the remote region in northern Afghanistan devastated by Saturday's earthquake that has killed at least 4,000 people and left thousands more homeless. (TBC) ---- AFGHAN: RABBANI - APTV will also have pictures of Afghani leader Burhanuddin Rabbani visiting the earthquake area. (TBC) ---- FRANCE: STRIKE - Pilots for Air France, the official carrier for next week's World Cup, has stayed off the job for a second day. APTV will have coverage of the strike causing chaos for more than 100,000.  (First run 1300 F-l-a-s-h) ---- US: SPACE - APTV has a feature on the future of US-Russian cooperation in space.  Pictures include, Russian space station Mir, space shuttle missions, international space station and interviews with NASA officials and astronauts. (First run 1440 Eurovision Window) ---- N'LANDS: SANDCASTLES - Scheveningen beach in the Netherlands is the latest site for a sand castle spectacular. APTV is there to get pictures of the 12 elaborate sand castles being constructed. (TBC) ---- HAGUE: WAR CRIMES - Milojica Kos, a Bosnian Serb indicted for wartime atrocities against Muslims and Croats at a prison camp, will enter a plea at his arraignment before the Yugoslav war crimes tribunal at the Hague. APTV will have coverage. (Europe Late 1500) ---- ALBANIA: REFUGEES - APTV is expecting pictures from Serbia's explosive Kosovo province where thousands of refugees are fleeing the deadliest fighting in months. (TBC) ---- BOSNIA: GERMANY - APTV will have coverage of German Defence Minister Volker Ruehe's visit to Bosnia. (F-l-a-s-h after 1645 gmt) ---- NIRELAND: BLAIR - British Prime Minister Tony Blair arrived in Northern Ireland on Tuesday for talks with Northern Ireland's political parties.  APTV will have pictures of the visit. (Europe Late 1500) ---- US: NAZI GOLD - A new US government reports says neutral nations kept Nazi Germany's war machine running with hundreds of millions of dollars of trade in key materials.  APTV's package will include the news conference by Stuart Eizenstadt, Undersecretary of State for Economics who is the author of the report. (Europe Late 1500) ---- RUNNING: ---- GENEVA: DISARMAMENT - APTV has coverage of the UN Conference on Disarmament holding an emergency meeting on Tuesday to discuss the fallout from the news that both India and Pakistan have tested nuclear weapons in the last month.  In a joint statement, 46 countries said the tests threatened the goal of nuclear disarmament. (First ran 1130 Europe Update) ---- SWITZERLAND: LABOUR - APTV has pictures of a protest march by hundreds of children ending a five month global march aimed at stamping out child labour.  Package also includes protests inside the International Labour Organisation and sound from the Director General of the ILO. (First run 1130 gmt Europe Update) ---- RUSSIA: TAX 2 - Amid a worsening economic crisis, Russian President Boris Yeltsin  has blasted the country's financial chiefs over their inability to collect taxes.  APTV has pictures of Yeltsin meeting with financial chiefs, the Union of Russian Taxpayers founding congress and comments from Russia's new tax tsar, Boris Fyodorov. (First ran 1130 Europe Update) ---- GREENPEACE: GLACIERS -  As a UN conference dedicated to finding an agreement on global cuts to greenhouse gases reopens in Bonn, environmentalists are warning that a rapid increase in regional temperatures has already caused North American glaciers to retreat and thin.  APTV has pictures from Prince William Sound and Majuro in the South Pacific where sea levels are rising on the low lying islands.  (First ran 1130 Europe Update) ---- ISRAEL: NUCLEAR - An Israeli spokesman has denied Israeli news reports that Tel Aviv planned to bomb Pakistan's nuclear installations ahead of the Islamic country's tests last month. APTV's package includes Prime Minister spokesman David Bar-Ilan denying these reports. (First ran Europe Morning 0800) ---- INDONESIA: DEMO 2 - The new Indonesian Government continues the pace of reform but some student demonstrators are still dissatisfied. APTV has pictures of student demonstrators in Jakarta and Ujungpandang and presser by Attorney General Sudjono Atmonegoro on the investigation into corruption under Suharto. (First ran 0715 Asia Pacific Late) ---- THAI: MILITARY - APTV has pictures of the final day of the Cobra Gold exercise, the annual military extravaganza in which Thai and US forces combine joint exercises. (First ran Asia Pacific Late 0715) ---- Editor of the Day: - 44 171 427 4163 Master Control Room - 44 171 427 4131 ---- APTV       (PROFILE (REG:ASIA;) (REG:ENGL;) (REG:EURO;) (REG:BRIT;) (REG:SCAN;) (REG:MEST;) (REG:AFRI;) (REG:INDI;) (LANG:ENGLISH;)) ) 

