 BC-Puerto Rico-Flash Flood Watch,0222 

Flash Flood Watch from the National Weather Service  BULLETIN-IMMEDIATE BROADCAST REQUESTED FLASH FLOOD WATCH NATIONAL WEATHER SERVICE SAN JUAN PR 1240 PM AST TUE JUN 2 1998  ...A FLASH FLOOD WATCH IS IN EFFECT FOR NORTH AND NORTHWEST SECTIONS    OF PUERTO RICO UNTIL 630 PM FROM SAN JUAN WEST TO AGUADILLA...    AND ALSO INCLUDES MOCA...SAN SEBASTIAN...AND LARES...  AFTERNOON SHOWERS AND THUNDERSTORMS HAVE BEGUN TO DEVELOP ACROSS NORTHWEST AND NORTH COASTAL SECTIONS OF PUERTO RICO TODAY...AND ARE EXPECTED TO INTENSIFY DURING THE AFTERNOON HOURS. THESE SHOWERS AND THUNDERSTORMS WILL LIKELY MOVE SLOWLY THIS AFTERNOON...CREATING A POTENTIAL TO PRODUCE VERY HEAVY RAINFALL ACROSS WET AND SATURATED SOILS. FOR THIS REASON...THE THREAT FOR FLASH FLOODING EXISTS THIS AFTERNOON ACROSS THE WATCH AREA. THE NATIONAL WEATHER SERVICE HAS THEREFORE ISSUED A FLASH FLOOD WATCH EFFECTIVE UNTIL 630 PM THIS EVENING FOR NORTH AND NORTHWEST SECTIONS OF THE ISLAND.  AREA RESIDENTS SHOULD MONITOR FLOOD CONDITIONS...AND BE PREPARED TO MOVE TO HIGHER GROUND SHOULD FLOOD WATERS THREATEN. IF FLASH FLOODING IS OBSERVED... ACT QUICKLY. MOVE TO HIGHER GROUND TO ESCAPE FLOOD WATERS. DO NOT STAY IN AREAS SUBJECT TO FLOODING WHEN WATER BEGINS RISING.        (PROFILE (REG:CRB;) (REG:ENGL;) (LANG:ENGLISH;)) ) 

